This guidebook reports Altemps Palace as belonging to its most recent owners, the Pallavicini-Rospigliosi family (about 1704–present). It does not mention the chain of previous owners: Scipione Borghese Caffarelli (1577–1633), about 1605–1616; Duke Giovanni Angelo Altemps (1587–1620), about 1616–1619; Guido Bentivoglio (1579–1644); Cardinal Giulio Mazarino (1602–1661), until about 1704; and the Pallavicini-Rospigliosi family, about 1704–present.
This guidebook mentions the location of the Roman Seminary in the Borromeo Palace (ex-Gabrielli) in Via del Seminario between 1608 and 1772.
